				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><span class="programlisting"><pre>&lt;STYLE type="text/css" media="print"&gt;...&lt;/STYLE&gt;</pre>
						</span></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="CLEARSEPARATION">&#160;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="value"><span class="title">Valeur</span></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><p>Constante sensible &agrave; la casse. Plusieurs valeurs peuvent &ecirc;tre regroup&eacute;es (elles seront alors s&eacute;par&eacute;es par des virgules) au sein d'une liste incluse entre guillemets. Les valeurs d&eacute;finies en HTML 4 sont les suivantes: <span class="literal">all</span> | <span class="literal">aura</span> | <span class="literal">braille</span> | <span class="literal">handheld</span> | <span class="literal">print</span> | <span class="literal">projection</span> | <span class="literal">screen</span> | <span class="literal">tty</span> | <span class="literal">tv</span> . Les valeurs reconnues par Internet Explorer sont les suivantes: <span class="literal">all</span> | <span class="literal">print</span> |<span class="literal">screen</span>.</p>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="CLEARSEPARATION">&#160;</td>
